```

## Installation
```
pnpmnpmyarnbunpnpm dlx shadcn@latest add badgeCopy
```


```
pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add badge
```


```
pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add badge
```

## Usage
```
Copyimport { Badge } from "@/components/ui/badge"
```


```
import { Badge } from "@/components/ui/badge"
```


```
Copy<Badge variant="default | outline | secondary | destructive">Badge</Badge>
```


```
<Badge variant="default | outline | secondary | destructive">Badge</Badge>
```

### Variants
Use the variant prop to change the variant of the badge.

```
variant
```


```
import { Badge } from "@/components/ui/badge" export function BadgeVariants() {
```


```
import { Badge } from "@/components/ui/badge" export function BadgeVariants() {
```

### With Icon
You can render an icon inside the badge. Use data-icon="inline-start" to render the icon on the left and data-icon="inline-end" to render the icon on the right.

```
data-icon="inline-start"
```


```
data-icon="inline-end"
```


```
import { Badge } from "@/components/ui/badge" import { BadgeCheck, BookmarkIcon } from "lucide-react"
```


```
import { Badge } from "@/components/ui/badge" import { BadgeCheck, BookmarkIcon } from "lucide-react"
```

### With Spinner
You can render a spinner inside the badge. Remember to add the data-icon="inline-start" or data-icon="inline-end" prop to the spinner.

```
data-icon="inline-start"
```


```
data-icon="inline-end"
```


```
import { Badge } from "@/components/ui/badge" import { Spinner } from "@/components/ui/spinner"
```


```
import { Badge } from "@/components/ui/badge" import { Spinner } from "@/components/ui/spinner"
```

### Link
Use the asChild prop to render a link as a badge.

```
asChild
```

[Open Link](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components/badge#link)

```
import { Badge } from "@/components/ui/badge" import { ArrowUpRightIcon } from "lucide-react"
```


```
import { Badge } from "@/components/ui/badge" import { ArrowUpRightIcon } from "lucide-react"
```

### Custom Colors
You can customize the colors of a badge by adding custom classes such as bg-green-50 dark:bg-green-800 to the Badge component.

```
bg-green-50 dark:bg-green-800
```


